==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: catbrier
<hw>catbrier</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a very prickly woody vine of
eastern U.S. (<spn>Smilax rotundifolia</spn>) growing in tangled masses,
having tough round stems with shiny leathery leaves and small greenish
flowers followed by clusters of inedible shiny black berries.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bullbrier, greenbrier, horsebrier, brier, briar,
<spn>Smilax rotundifolia</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catcall</ent>⟦br⟧
